items.name: Cucumber-play
items.description:
My first Lora Model here for some Veggie fun playing around with cucumbers^^

By using and mixing the tags you might get different poses - in a next version i'll try to focus more on those tags and train few steps shorter.

Notes:
a) Use a lora weight 0.8 or 0.9
b) Put trigger word "ccmbr" in front of prompts (don't force use "cucumber" in addition, otherwise maybe too many will appear)
c) Recommended to use at least min. 3 tags in combination but don't use all tags together
d) Generally use minimum CFG scale 7 or try higher !!

e.g. by simply using these thre positive prompts "<lora:ccmbr_v1.0:0.8> ccmbr, kneeling, pussy-insertion" and CFG=9 i did get working results with 3 different models in a quick test.

It was trained with URPM but it should work with diff. realistic models - but also some anime models worked surprisingly well.

Have a look at the last example image grid - there you can see that it works best with weight between 0.7 and 0.9

Have fun and let's see your results...

items.name: "Trending on ArtStation" trained without a dataset
items.description:
Training does not require a dataset, only words.

Trained in 2400 steps (about 7 hrs on 2 a6000s) using only text with:
https://github.com/ntc-ai/conceptmod

Training prompt for the first 2000 steps:
"=trending on artstation, 8k, ultra hd|boring=exciting|drab=captivating|1woman%generic woman wearing generic clothes:0.003|1woman%woman wearing many unique tasteful accessories and a cute outfit:-0.003|@monochrome--|@black and white--|@text--|@written words--"

  • Pulls the unconditional towards "trending on artstation, 8k, ultra hd"

  • Replaces Pulls "boring" to "exciting" and "drab" to "captivating".
    Update: this doesn't replace. It pulls towards. Replace needs an additional % term, see the readme.md

  • Reduces the occurrence of "monochrome", "black and white", "text", and "written words".

  • Slightly blends 1woman away from "generic woman wearing generic clothes"

  • Slightly blends 1woman towards "woman wearing many unique tasteful accessories and a cute outfit"
    Update: I think these terms might be backwards. LOL


Training prompt for the next 400 steps:
"@#|1woman=ugly manly sad wretched:-0.1|1woman=woman wearing many unique tasteful accessories and a cute outfit|nipples--:0.1|cleavage--:0.01"

  • Freezes the unconditional concept using the "@#" operator.

  • Reduces the occurrence of "nipples" by 0.1 and "cleavage" by 0.01.

Technique based on https://github.com/rohitgandikota/erasing
Model based on https://civitai.com/models/13565/criarcys-fantasy-to-experience

items.name: Animals - AutoPrompt - Awesome prompt lists
items.description:
Description

🐾✨ Dive into an animal wildcard pack that sparks wonder and captivates the senses! 🎨🌿 Discover captivating studies, endearing displays, and evocative portraits of animals. From striking outfits to Renaissance-inspired paintings, each image style is a visual delight. 🌈🦜 Let your imagination soar as animals thrive in fantasy realms and rustic containers. This pack offers a diverse range of animal images, invoking emotions and inviting contemplation. 📸🐾 #AnimalArt #CaptivatingCreatures #ImaginativeDelights

Usage

Useful for when you want to create images and later go through and pick out the best creations. These prompts are randomly generated every time I generate new lists.

I use them in conjunction with a stable diffusion image viewer I have written where I view thousands of images I've created to find:

  1. Good prompts that have an art style I like

  2. Good prompts that create really good images

  3. Good compositions

How to use prompt files

  1. Open automatic1111 SD / any other SD creation tool with similar prompt file input

  2. Select <Script> --> Prompts from file or textbox

  3. Drop file or copy paste contents in the "List of prompts inputs"

  4. To view information on images you have created you can use "PNG Info" tab in Automatic1111.

items.name: [SD 1.5] Pokemon - Hilda / Touko
items.description:
Please read through the entire description (might need to be expanded) and the version change notes as they cover a lot of information about basic use cases and limitations. The description is always focused on the latest version. Thank you!

This is an SD 1.5 LoRA for the character Hilda / Touko from Pokemon. It works for models based on SD 1.x only, it will not work for models based on SD 2.x or SDXL!

Example images were picked from pure 512x512 txt2img results and then re-created at 1024x1024 using txt2img with moderate Hi-res Fix settings (upscaler Lanczos, denoising strength 0.4). This improves faces and other details that are almost impossible to get correctly and consistently at 512x512 (limitation of the technology) while still giving a realistic impression of what it looks like. Pure 512x512 results will have more distorted faces and less detail.

Please see the version change notes for the training and example image generation models as well as the used weights as they might change between versions. Remember that you might need to adjust weights to best suit your use case!

Remember to add the tag hilda \(pokemon\) (with backslashes intact) to your positive prompt.

The training set contained multiple variations of Hilda's signature look so you might need to put combinations of the following tags in your positive or negative prompts to get the desired results:

  • baseball cap

  • boots

  • shorts

  • shoulder bag

  • sleeveless shirt

  • socks

  • vest

  • wristband

  • xtransceiver (the wristwatch-like device)

As the training set contained a few images with floating hair, you might need to add floating hair to the negative prompts if not desired.

Known Limitations / Problems:

  • The boots, socks and xtransceiver were not present in a lot of images and not a focus for the training so they sadly will not be consistent.

  • The exposed pockets (or whatever they are) from the shorts are very inconsistent, especially when sitting and from behind (they seem to be mostly missing then).

    • They will also often affect alternative clothing like panties etc. which will then appear with the same exposed pockets and perhaps even denim material as the shorts. Putting extra weight on both shorts in the negative prompts and the alternative clothing in the positive prompts might help but not by a lot.

  • Might generate a lot of midriff peeks or similar visible gaps underneath the shirt

    • Try midriff peek and similar tags in the negative prompts

  • It seems to be very difficult to remove the sleeveless shirt and vest separately from each other.

    • Keeping only the vest seems especially difficult and luck-based.

    • Might need additional weight in the negative prompts (but even then it's very inconsistent).

    • Even when it works, the color of e.g. the vest might mix into the sleeveless shirt etc.

  • The hair might come out of wrong spots in the baseball cap (or not at all), especially from behind, and is pretty wild and inconsistent in general

    • Basically, good luck getting the hair to look like you want!

    • To be fair, that is also the case for a lot of regular Hilda art.

  • Shots from behind are very inconsistent in general due to extremely limited training data. Might for instance generate wrong hair, not apply poses correctly etc. Not much I can do without a bit more training data.

  • The baseball cap might require additional weight in the negative prompt to remove. Still, it just loves to pop up. How nice!

modelVersions.name: v3
modelVersions.description:
There are detailed changes below the next paragraph, you might need to expand this version changes box!

I learned a few new things about creating LoRAs and wanted to see how far I can push my existing LoRAs without changes to their datasets (well... not quite for this one, see below). So there's still no support for alternate outfits, colors etc. for now, sorry! There are other LoRAs if you want those things. Not sure if I'll improve the LoRAs more than that in the future or make new ones but who knows.

(Had a LOT of issues with this one in particular, might not be that great but I am done investing more time into it honestly)

LoRA Changes:

  • Now uses the standard "hilda \(pokemon\)" instead of a custom trigger word to make things easier for everyone (please note though that the LoRA itself is still named "character_pokemon_hilda_vX" as before!)

  • Switch to 32 dims (now trained directly instead of resizing from 128)

  • Switch to target weight 1 (increased from 0.7)

  • Changed a lot of training settings (too many to list, check LoRA metadata if you are interested) and updated to much newer scripts version (~3 months worth of changes)

  • I had to remove six (!) images from the dataset as they confused the new training too much. As a result, details in all sorts of situations might sadly become a bit worse in general and especially for close-ups. Hopefully not much else gets worse.

  • Added a new tag "xtransceiver" (the wristwatch-like device) to perhaps make the wristbands more consistent.

Example image changes:

  • Use CLIP skip 2 instead of 1 as I accidentally did before

  • Change settings for hir-res fix: Switch upscaler from None to Lanczos and increase denoise from 0.1 to 0.4 to get better results while still not changing TOO much

  • Use a negative embedding for the majority of negative prompting

Recommended weight: 1

Training model: Anything V3

Example image generation model: AbyssOrangeMix2 - Hardcore

items.name: Butt plug
items.description:
Butt Plug v1.1

I was surprised to find that there is no such thing on this site yet, so I decided to take a swing at it myself.

The results are a mixed bag. I am surprised that the model has learned anything at all, especially how the object in question should look and where it should be located relative to the body. Sometimes it does quite well, but it also tends to noticeably worsen overall quality of the picture (seems that the LoRA learned much more than what I intended). If you have a lot of patience you can fix its shortcomings to some extent by using inpainting.

This is my first experience with LoRA training, and I'm sure I've made a lot of stupid mistakes that could have been avoided. I look forward to your comments and suggestions on how this model can be improved.

I'll also be glad if my example inspires someone else to try to achieve better results.

I want to do some more experiments with this concept when I have time, in particular I think about trying to:

  • improve the quality of the dataset some more

  • manually verify and fix all generated image descriptions

  • prepare a regularization dataset

  • try using constant LR

不需要太多的介绍了，每个人都喜欢或者讨厌女武神，至少她在游戏里狠狠的虐待了我们。我尝试去做出更好看的第二形态，但是由于两者差别太大，可能需要另一个模型来实现了。总之好好享受，下面是一些建议:

Not much introduction is needed, everyone either loves or hates Malenia, at least she has been a fierce opponent in the game. I tried to create a better-looking second form, but due to the significant difference between the two, another model may be needed to achieve it. Anyway, enjoy, here are some suggestions:

  1. 使用0.2-0.9的权重都有比较好的效果, 0.2-0.4属于风格化转换。

  2. 为了能过够分开左右手的区别，我增加了单独的右手触发单词，并且为了可调节性，我分开了不少触发词，这样可以做大脱面具，请大家一定仔细阅读下面的关键词：主触发词eldenring\(malenia\), 可能可以触发eldenring\(type2\), 其他触发cursed_left_arm, winged helmet, red cape, malenia_blade, covered eyes 其中 cursed_left_arm可以触发左右的腐蚀效果，帮助SD区分左右手，去除winged helmet和 covered eyes, 并将他们加入到反向提示词，同时增加beautiful face的特征描述，就能把面具脱下来，看到我给你们添加的惊喜，希望你们能喜欢。

  3. 模型融入了女武神场景，默认就会触发，当然你也可以更改。背面的披风图片较少，可能较难触发，请多测试几次，背面披风很好看，一定要看到哦。

  4. 推荐模型： chilloutmix, prefect world, Dalcefo, AOM, anything, 和所有你希望尝试的模型。

大家的支持才让我有动力再继续带来高质量的lora

  1. Using weights between 0.2-0.9 produces good results, with 0.2-0.4 being suitable for stylized transformation.

  2. In order to distinguish between left and right hand movements, I added a separate trigger word for the right hand, and to allow for adjustability, I separated several trigger words. This allows for the creation of a full face reveal. Please read the following keywords carefully: main trigger word eldenring\(malenia\), which may trigger eldenring\(type2\), other triggers include "cursed_left_arm", "winged helmet", "red cape", "malenia_blade", and "covered eyes". The trigger word "cursed_left_arm" can trigger left and right corrosion effects to help distinguish between left and right hands. Removing the "winged helmet" and "covered eyes", and adding them to the reverse trigger words, while adding a feature description for "beautiful face", will allow the mask to be removed and reveal the surprises I have added for you. I hope you like it.

  3. The model incorporates the Malenio located scene by default, but you can also customize it. There are fewer images of the cloak on the back, making it more difficult to trigger, so please test it several times. The cloak on the back is very beautiful, so be sure to see it.

  4. Recommended models: chilloutmix, prefect world, Dalcefo, AOM, anything, and any other models you want to try.

Your support gives me the motivation to continue bringing you high-quality Lora.

items.name: Minolta Reflex 500mm Style
items.description:
基于Minolta Reflex 500mm镜头所拍摄照片训练的真实性风格。体现出该镜头所拥有的景深、色彩、光斑、对比度等特性。适用于具有高度真实性的摄影照片，作为超级长焦镜头极浅景深的特点，使其在Stable Diffusion 中要特别注意构图，特别是主体与背景的关系。

触发词：500R,

描述扩展：Depth of Field, Bokeh,bokeh background,

为了提高镜头特有的甜甜圈散景光斑，可以提高背景的光照，例如添加“bright background ”等。

权重可以设置高一些。

Authentic style trained on photos taken with the Minolta Reflex 500mm lens. It reflects the depth of field, color, spot, contrast and other characteristics of the lens. It is suitable for photographic photos with a high degree of realism. As a super telephoto lens with extremely shallow depth of field, special attention must be paid to composition in Stable Diffusion, especially the relationship between the subject and the background.

Trigger words: 500R,

Description extension: Depth of Field, Bokeh, bokeh background,

In order to improve the lens-specific donut bokeh spots, you can increase the background lighting, such as adding "bright background" and so on.

The weight can be set higher.

items.name: Belial (Granblue Fantasy) LoCon

You can support me on Ko-fi ☕ if you like my work.

Use the tag belial \(granblue fantasy\) as well as other descriptive tags (short hair, black hair, red eyes), to trigger Belial's looks.

Recommended Weight: 0.5 - 0.6.

0.6 is good for reproducing Belial's canonical outfit.

Tags to reproduce Belial's canon outfit: black shirt, feather boa, belt, black pants

This LoCon can also reproduce Belial's Avatar form, although the details are not quite right. These are the additional tags I used to train the looks of Avatar Belial: avatar belial, black sclera, mismatched sclera, torn clothes, open shirt, horns, facial tattoo, chest tattoo, arm tattoo, wings. You can try if you'd like!

You can try this LoCon on any checkpoints that support Danbooru tags, and other style LoRAs.

How to use

  • Select any checkpoint that works with Danbooru tags. Recommended models: AnyLoRA or AOM series.

  • Select a VAE if the checkpoint model you're using doesn't have a baked-in VAE, or else you'll find your generated images have dull colors. You can use vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned, kl-f8-anime2, or NAI VAE.

  • Make sure to follow the steps in How to use a LoCon. I suggest you start by setting the weight to 0.5.

  • Generate at 512 base resolution and use hires fix to improve the details. Recommended upscaler: R-ESRGAN 4x+ Anime6B; denoising strength: 0.5.

items.name: Combine Soldier - Half-Life
items.description:
Overwatch, 742 at grid 9-7. Holding for advanced directive.

This is a lora trained on 24 hand picked images of Combine Soldiers from Half Life 2. It was trained mostly on digital art, but there are some 3d renders in there for variety. It was kind of hard finding quality art of just combine soldiers online, so there are only 24 images in this set. I was also planning on having this be trained on both combine soldiers and combine elite soldiers, but changed my last last minute. It was trained on danbooru-style tags, so use those when trying to prompt - I've included the tags in a .txt file in the "Training Images" download below.

It works pretty well with most .ckpts, but I recommend Anything 4.5 or AOM3A1B, I used them for the example images.

NOTES:

-Make sure to specify the color of the glowing eye-holes, I forgot to do that for most of the example images so sometimes different colors show up. It should be able to do red, or blue colored easily natively, but also other colors if you emphasize it enough.

-A good amount of images were trained with characters holding guns, so its slightly better at doing that than usual.

-The armor vest can be a little iffy, and sometimes it won't look exactly like the combine armor usually does.

Example prompt: (See example images, all images should still have their metadata. Just drag the images onto the PNG info tab and import it.)

items.name: Combine Assassin - Half-Life
items.description:
The Combine Assassin! She was a character cut from Half-Life 2 before release. Not to be confused for the Combine Elite soldiers that the concept was turned into.

This is a lora trained on 22 hand picked images of the Combine Assassin that was cut from Half Life 2. It was trained mostly on digital art, but there are some 3d renders in there for variety. This character is basically a female version of the Combine Elite enemies. She was supposed to be akin to those Black-Op Assassins from Half-Life 1. It was trained on danbooru-style tags, so use those when trying to prompt - I've included the tags in a .txt file in the "Training Images" download below.

It works pretty well with most .ckpts, but I recommend Anything 4.5 or AOM3A1B, I used them for the example images.

NOTES:

-She seems to be a little shy, and has a hard time facing directly forward, or looking directly at viewer, even when prompted

-The small armor vest can be a little iffy, but that's about the only inconsistency on this.

Example prompt: (See example images, all images should still have their metadata. Just drag the images onto the PNG info tab and import it.)

items.name: bad_pictures
items.description:
A very versatile negative embedding that helps generate high quality images. Higher chances of producing normal looking hands in realistic images.

Best Practices:

Keep your token usage to below 75 for best effect. Most of the time, you don't need to add other quality specifiers to your prompts (e.g. worst quality, bad quality).

Usage:

Negative prompt: bad_pictures

If you notice any artifacts, you can try increasing or decreasing the weighting like this: (bad_pictures:1.1) or (bad_pictures:0.8).

Values between 0.8 and 1.2 seems to work best (clip size 2):

Tested on:

  • VersaMix (https://civitai.com/models/20865/versamix)

  • Lyriel (https://civitai.com/models/22922/lyriel)

  • Anything V5 (https://civitai.com/models/9409?modelVersionId=30163)
